    {
      "task": "Anyone else experiencing similar customer feedback?\n\nOne of my customers is extremely frustrated with the volume of emails generated by Process Governance, particularly since the release of the approval expiration feature. With more than 2,000 processes in Signavio and a large number of participants (stakeholders, reviewers, etc.), many users are receiving unnecessary notifications, such as daily approval-expiration reminders which leads to frustration and is already being cited as a potential reason to reconsider the renewal of Signavio. There is an existing product request on the product board addressing this topic, see here.\n\nRequest: Please share any insights, feedback, or roadmap updates you have. Thanks&nbsp;",
      "mentioned_by": "Neumeier, Veronika",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-20T12:39:43.747Z"
    },
    {
      "task": "\nHello&nbsp;Neumeier,&nbsp;Veronika.&nbsp;\nYou could decrease amount of the notifications from Process Governance, by removing the Newsletter preferences in the settings.&nbsp;\nIt will not remove all the emails, however will significantly decrease the amount. &nbsp;\nhttps://help.sap.com/docs/signavio-process-governance/user-guide/my-profile?q=settings+notification\u2026",
      "mentioned_by": "Schedl, Maryna",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-20T13:23:15.336Z"
    },
    {
      "task": "\nworkflow notifications are in the scope of Maryna. What happens on general suite notifications will not affect workflow notifications. Neumeier,&nbsp;Veronika&nbsp;for your process governance specific inquiry notifications can be reduced as Maryna mentioned.&nbsp;",
      "mentioned_by": "Rotaru, Adriana",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-20T17:58:37.694Z"
    },
    {
      "task": "Hi team, I hope all is well. I\u2019m working with BC Hydro on their Signavio rollout, and they\u2019re looking for clear guidance on how best to handle user onboarding and license management.\nSpecifically, they\u2019d like to understand all available options for:\n1. User provisioning\nManual user creation (current approach)\nAutomatic/SSO-based provisioning (e.g., granting access to users or specific groups in an automated fashion)\nAny common hybrid models\n2. License optimization\nWhether licenses can be automatically revoked after inactivity (e.g., 60 days) and then re-granted when needed\nBest practices you see with other customers to avoid large numbers of inactive users\n3. Use of Joule AI admin agent\nWhat the Joule AI admin agent can do today for user provisioning and license/admin automation\nHow it typically complements or replaces the options above, and any key limitations or prerequisites\nCould you also share:\nThe recommended patterns you see with customers, and\nAny pros/cons or standard setups (including Joule) that we should consider for BC Hydro?\n&nbsp;\nAny help will be appreciated. Thanks&nbsp;",
      "mentioned_by": "Chibeze, Manny",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-23T19:52:11.023Z"
    }
